hungry Sunday
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:Sunday overtime, applied for, and worked by one `hungry for money'.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (Wellington tramways) ca1950 F.M. O'Brien To have hungry Sunday (or h. call-back) = `Of those who, hungry for money, accept overtime joyfully, and apply for it' (call-back is a notification of extra (overtime) shift-work, ie. called back on duty)
